Vomit! "We knew . We we we" yeah GB you didn't know jack and it showed. The jags didn't need a first time head coach ; the jags needed a hard nosed proven head coach. We got another "players coach" and one that is "learning" on the job as he goes. A combo recipe that equaled abysmal failure. I hate to throw cold water on this puff piece by the Jags "senior" writer who was hired by the khan regime to be a PR water boy; but this is it GB. You are in year 3 of your hideous head coaching experience and if history from around the NFL has taught us anything it's that the 3rd year in a head coaches career is the make or break year. That is if you failed to get close to the playoffs which you have never even seen the tunnel for. I know a lot of the same Jag fans are already in full hype mode and will really start filling your head with confidence as you win 3 of the 4 pre-season games and they will be bragging on this FB page about how the jags are back to 1998 form.... But sadly just like last season, reality really does hit like a ton of bricks GB as you begin the slow and painful decent into a sub par downward spiral. Then by mid season when our arch enemy the Titans kick our butt for the second time and the playoff missing fate is sealed you will then know that you were way over your positive head!
